[49m[38;5;9m- 27    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m The validator is a four-layer check applied to every narrative: schema and length, fact grounding (every clinical claim traces to a structured element of the recommendation record or the regime catalog), prohibited-language patterns (no recommendation language for treatments not in the regime's action catalog, no probabilistic claims framed as guarantees, no policy-as-directive framing), and required content (uncertainty disclosure, regime-version reference, override-encouragement framing for the clinician narrative; care-plan-linkage and contact-for-questions for the patient narrative). Failed validations regenerate with feedback or fall back to a templated narrative.
